04/08/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Former Prime Minister Ilir Meta said Tuesday (3 August) that the Socialist Movement for Integration, which he formed several months ago, will officially evolve into a political party in September, in time for the autumn parliamentary season. It will then be known as the Socialist Party for Integration. Meta said the party would likely run in the June 2005 general elections. (Albanian Daily News - 04/08/04)
